The blind albino cavefish actually have small eyes that form as embryos but eventually break down, sink into the eye orbit, and are covered by skin. The blind cave fish will even construct the lens and retina but eventually they hit a point where their cells stop constructing and self terminate. These fish don’t only live in caves but actually have relatives that live on the surface that are still colored and have completely functional eyes. So if a god created blind cave fish, why would he or she have given them useless eyes, which perfectly match with the surface forms of the same creature?


