One great thing about the fossil record is that it is ordered from oldest to youngest, naturally. Not only do the dates found with dating techniques fit the order of the layers, but within the layers the fossils always show the steps of evolution in order. (If layers are out of order, it can always be traced to natural causes that leave signs.) <br><br>

Different layers are exposed around the world that represent different time periods and different animals. We can then look back into time below the layers and we’ll find the older dates and older forms. We can also take these known layers and find the missing newer layers somewhere else and continue the transition of dates and forms. We’ve never found a single fossil out of place that couldn’t be explained. If evolution is so wrong, why is so easy to predict what we will find next, down to the layer, age, and type of form?


