Each of these layers record not only the animals present, but also the vegetation, climate, magnetic poles, oxygen content, flooding, and many more things. The complexity of these will fit into the layer puzzle in order. 

A human will never appear before fossil primates. A primate will never appear before fossil mammals. A mammal or bird will never appear before fossil reptiles. A reptile or amphibian will never appear before fossil fish. A fish will never be found before the first chordates, spanning back 550 million years ago.

If obvious order of the fossil record does not show the evolution of complexity, what then does it mean? Can you claim that a flood will create this order without even ONE misplacement? Why do fish sink before everything except the simple chordates? Why does the fossil record not show flooding through the whole series of layers?


